page.title: 04ANNETTE SMITH'S SCHOOL DAY
page.content: Annette Smith is aged 13 and lives in Sudbrooke. I get up at 7.45 am and get ready for school.At 8.30 I make my way to Scothern by bike to catch the school bus to welton. School starts at 9.10. We have eight 35 min lessons during the day with a break during the morning and afternoon and 1 hour 5 mins for lunch. At 3.45 we go home. I get off the school bus and then cycle back to Sudbrooke. When I get home the Lincolnshire Echo is waiting on the doorstep ready to be delivered. After this I then have my tea and do my homework until about 7pm. I then read or watch television depending on what is on. I always watch Dallas and Dynasty. I usually go to bed at 9.30 and read by this time I am very tired.
